### Example 3 — ACCUMULATION pattern: double bottom on RSI divergence

Indicators: 2 lows printed at 75320 (separated 8 candles), second low with RSI 28 vs first at 24 (bullish divergence). MACD hist negative but rising (-12 → -4). EMA20 75600, price 75450 (below). Volume on second low: 1.3× MA20 (light, but in line with the compression context). Daily regime `sideways`, weekly position 0.18 (near weekly low). EQH cluster above at 75900 ×2.

Multi-touch + divergence = accumulation. Volume light is OK in compression context (per volume matrix). 2 concordant signals (double bottom + RSI div), no event trigger, no daily regime tailwind → moderate score.

